So, when a = -1, one of the roots is y = 0. Therefore, in this case, the roots are y = 0 and y = -1/2. So, y = 0 corresponds to x = π/2, and y = -1/2 corresponds to x = 2π/3. So, two solutions. Therefore, when a = -1, there are two solutions. So, even though one root is zero, it only gives one solution (x = π/2) and the other root gives x = 2π/
